    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** lineup is positioned for a high-output Tuesday, anchored by elite plays against favorable matchups. **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.87) represent our strongest daily starters; **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 15% SP skill boost against Wacha, while **Kyle Tucker** leverages his high-floor offensive profile despite a slight park disadvantage. **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) is also a standout, utilizing an incredible +14% park factor and a +17% SP skill advantage to vault into the upper echelon of today\u2019s projected production. Our infield efficiency is bolstered by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.55) and **Nasim Nunez** (68.23), both of whom take advantage of the generous 5.07 xERA provided by Didier Fuentes.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Marcell Ozuna** (60.81). Despite a strong score that narrowly outclasses **Dominic Smith** (54.77), **Marcell Ozuna** was excluded because of the optimizer's reliance on fixed roster slots and the specific need to balance our categorical efficiency. While **Marcell Ozuna**\u2019s power profile is undeniable, the current construction prioritizes the speed-driven upside of **Nasim Nunez** and the consistent hitting environment surrounding **Dominic Smith**. We continue to monitor all \"Lineup Pending\" designations\u2014specifically for **Drake Baldwin**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Brady House**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Miguel Vargas**\u2014as any shuffle in batting order could significantly fluctuate these projected scores. \n\nRisk remains concentrated in the pitching matchups; while most of our hitters face pitchers with xERAs above 4.00, we are keeping a close watch on **Liam Hicks** (46.57), whose lower score reflects a tougher-than-average assignment against Leahy. Additionally, weather-aided wind at the venues for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Coby Mayo** (if pressed into service) provides a marginal boost, but players like **Andy Pages** must contend with a slight park-induced penalty. We are comfortable with today\u2019s alignment, balancing high-speed upside with the raw power metrics required to remain competitive in the 5x5 Roto standings.",
